# Drop curated photos in this directory tree.
#
#   public/images/projects/<projectId>/cover.jpg                      project tile cover
#   public/images/projects/<projectId>/groups/<groupId>.jpg           group tile hero
#   public/images/projects/<projectId>/species/<speciesId>.jpg        primary species plate
#
# Reference these from JSON content using a root-relative path, e.g.
#   "image": "/images/projects/indoor-insects/species/odorous-house-ant.jpg"
#
# A leading "assets/" prefix on any image path is stripped automatically
# (the prototype data used "assets/images/..." paths). New entries should
# use the "/images/..." form above.
#
# Empty / missing files render as the striped placeholder, so this
# directory can stay empty during editing — fill it in as photos are
# cleared for use.
